&Category=&Competition_ID=&Player_ID=101439&|publisher=[[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]]|date=1 June 2007|accessdate=21 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nDavis qualified for the Australian squad, as a 19-year-old teen, in two table tennis events at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in Beijing, by placing second in the men's singles from the Oceania Qualification Tournament in [[Noumea]], and receiving a continental spot for Oceania in the men's team under ITTF's Computer Team Ranking List.<ref>{{cite web|title=Players Qualified for the Olympic Games |url=http://www.ittf.com/World_Events/Olympic_games_2008/Olympics_08_players_list_Final_28_Jul_2008.pdf |format=[[PDF]] |publisher=[[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]] |accessdate=26 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815012958/http://ittf.com/World_Events/Olympic_games_2008/Olympics_08_players_list_Final_28_Jul_2008.pdf |archivedate=15 August 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Marshall|first=Ian|title=Emotional Scenes as Australians Secure Olympic Places in New Caledonia|url=http://www.ittf.com/_front_page/ittf_full_story1.asp?ID=15183&Competition_ID=1700&|publisher=[[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]]|date=7 April 2008|accessdate=21 October 2014}}</ref> Joining his fellow players [[William Henzell]] and [[David Zalcberg]] in the inaugural [[Table tennis at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team|men's team]] event, Davis and his Australian squad finished on the bottom of the prelim pool with three straight defeats against Greece, Austria, and the host nation China.<ref>{{cite web|title=Men's Team Group A (AUS\u2013GRE)|url=http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/tabletennis/resultsandschedules/rsc=TTM400A06/index.html|publisher=[[NBC Olympics]]|accessdate=25 February 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821153602/http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/tabletennis/resultsandschedules/rsc%3DTTM400A06/index.html|archive-date=21 August 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>