{"title_page": "Yuliya Novakovich", "text_new": "{{short description|Belarusian weightlifter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| headercolor = lightblue\n| name           = Yuliya Novakovich\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = Yuliya Siarheyeuna Novakovich\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{BLR}}\n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1989|5|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Pinsk]], [[Belarusian SSR]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{height|m=1.65|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = {{convert|74|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]]\n| event          =  75 kg\n| collegeteam    = \n| club           = Dynamo Mahilyow\n| team           =  \n| turnedpro      = \n| coach          =\n| retired        = \n| coaching       = \n| worlds         = \n| regionals      = \n| nationals      = \n| olympics       = \n| paralympics    = \n| highestranking = \n| pb             = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n\n'''Yuliya Siarheyeuna Novakovich''' ({{lang-be|\u042e\u043b\u0456\u044f \u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u045e\u043d\u0430 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0447}}; born May 6, 1989 in [[Pinsk]]) is a [[Belarus]]ian [[weightlifter]].<ref>{{cite sports-reference|Yuliya Novakovich|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/no/yuliya-novakovich-1.html|9 December 2012}}</ref> Novakovich represented Belarus at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], where she competed for the [[Weightlifting at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 75 kg|women's heavyweight category]], along with her compatriot [[Iryna Kulesha]], who eventually won the silver medal. She placed tenth in this event, as she successfully lifted 110&nbsp;kg in the [[snatch (weightlifting)|snatch]], and hoisted 127&nbsp;kg in the [[clean and jerk]], for a total of 237&nbsp;kg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Women's 75kg (165 lbs)|url=http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/weightlifting/resultsandschedules/rsc=WLW075000/standings.html|publisher=[[NBC Olympics]]|accessdate=9 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/athletes/athlete=66146/bio/index.html NBC 2008 Olympics profile] {{dead link|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Novakovich, Yuliya}}\n[[Category:Belarusian female weightlifters]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Olympic weightlifters of Belarus]]\n[[Category:Weightlifters at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from Pinsk]]\n\n\n{{Belarus-weightlifting-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belarusian weightlifter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| headercolor = lightblue\n| name           = Yuliya Novakovich\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = \n| caption        = \n| birth_name     = \n| fullname       = Yuliya Siarheyeuna Novakovich\n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{BLR}}\n| residence      = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1989|5|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Pinsk]], [[Belarusian SSR]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{height|m=1.65|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = {{convert|74|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}}\n| website        = \n| country        = \n| sport          = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]]\n| event          =  75 kg\n| collegeteam    = \n| club           = Dynamo Mahilyow\n| team           =  \n| turnedpro      = \n| coach          =\n| retired        = \n| coaching       = \n| worlds         = \n| regionals      = \n| nationals      = \n| olympics       = \n| paralympics    = \n| highestranking = \n| pb             = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n\n'''Yuliya Siarheyeuna Novakovich''' ({{lang-be|\u042e\u043b\u0456\u044f \u0421\u044f\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435\u045e\u043d\u0430 \u041d\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0456\u0447}}; born May 6,